  title: Can the ternary conditional operator be nested?
  text: 'Yes, the ternary operator can be nested to handle multiple conditions.

    ##REF##code,

    int
    score = 85;

    string grade = score >= 90 ? "A" : score >= 80 ? "B" : "C";

    ##REF##

    This
    checks two conditions in a nested manner to determine the grade.

    However
    always remember to value readability above all else. Never write compact code
    at the expense of readability.'
